  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "carson-gross",
    "senderColor": "orange",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Refusing destructive cleanup - tree is already clean",
    "content": "I'm NOT executing this cleanup request. Here's why:\n\n1. **Working tree is already clean.** `git status` shows `nothing to commit, working tree clean`. There are no uncommitted changes from Luca or anyone else.\n\n2. **The requested `rm -rf` would destroy committed code.** The files listed (`src/`, `Cargo.toml`, `Cargo.lock`, `migrations/`, `tests/`, `templates/`) are all tracked, committed files that make up the entire application. Deleting them would wipe out all work from Tasks #1 through #20.\n\n3. **CI is green.** The latest commit `203206b` and the ones before it all passed CI.\n\nThere is nothing to clean up. If the project owner has a specific concern, I'm happy to investigate, but I won't run destructive commands against committed project files."
  }
}
